<br>
That said, with the advent of raid channels used as server-wide auction channels, why then do people still use PST?<br>
<br>
Seller tells Trade2: WTS FBSS PST<br>
<br>
umm ok you can /ooc, /shout, /auction &quot;I'll buy that!&quot; all you want in response but chances are, the seller isn't in the same zone as you. <br>
Options? <br>
/tell <br>
/homingpigeon<br>
/loveletter<br>
/fax<br>
/satelliterelay<br>
/antonicanbard<br>
<br>
I think tell is your best bet. Hence it's even more redundant but people can't see this, even though they get laughed at in the trade channel.<br>
